	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It is actually not too diffucult to take Famitone sound effects code (it is designed to be well separated from music code there), and hook it to Famitracker player. It'll increase memory (RAM and ROM) and CPU use, though, but still may be acceptable for some games.
<br />
<br />And let's not forget about <a href="http://kkfos.aspekt.fi/projects/nes/muse/" class="postlink">MUSE</a>, another good engine to have music and sound effects.
<br />
<br />Another thing, a shameless plug - I have an experimental chiptune tracker project called <a href="http://shiru.untergrund.net/files/1tracker.zip" class="postlink">1tracker</a>, which easily could be used as front end for a custom NES music engine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


